,1,'2018-11-07 10:06:18','2018-11-07 10:06:18','Dress up your dogs in cute outfits!\r\nThey can offer some protection against the cold for your dogs, especially rainbow colored socks!\r\n\r\nAlso be mindful of salting and wax or protect your pets paws!','Winter is coming!','','inherit','closed','closed','','77-revision-v1','','','2018-11-07 10:06:18','2018-11-07 10:06:18','',77,'http://clinic.local/77-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(79,1,'2018-01-07 10:07:43','2018-01-07 10:07:43','How is this a real thing?\r\nCmon, its a loop over posts.\r\nIt should do the same for every post, unless the data is missing.\r\nBut its not missing, i just verified that it\'s there....\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nthe_date(); only displays date for the first element in a set of elements posted on the same day. Something related to the logic in the implementation. It will fail a check if the second post shares the same date.\r\n\r\nWorkaround:\r\nUse echo get_the_date(); instead!','Some posts lose their ability to display date','','publish','open','open','','some-posts-lose-their-ability-to-display-date','','','2018-11-08 10:09:01','2018-11-08 10:09:01','',0,'http://clinic.local/?p=79',0,'post','',0),(80,1,'2018-11-07 10:07:43','2018-11-07 10:07:43','How is this a real thing?\r\nCmon, its a loop over posts.\r\nIt should do the same for every post, unless the data is missing.\r\nBut its not missing, i just verified that it\'s there....\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWhats going on wordpress?','Some posts lose their ability to display date','','inherit','closed','closed','','79-revision-v1','','','2018-11-07 10:07:43','2018-11-07 10:07:43','',79,'http://clinic.local/79-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(81,1,'2018-11-07 10:14:05','2018-11-07 10:14:05','Most dogs love playing in the snow!\r\nDoes your pooch like snow?\r\nLet us know in the comments!','Snow','Oh how nice it is with snow. The season for playing outside all day, then rolling oneself up in a blanket with a good book in the evenings.','publish','open','open','','snow','','','2018-11-15 11:22:11','2018-11-15 11:22:11','',0,'http://clinic.local/?p=81',0,'post','',0),(82,1,'2018-11-07 10:14:05','2018-11-07 10:14:05','Most dogs love playing in the snow!\r\nDoes your pooch like snow?\r\nLet us know in the comments!','Snow','','inherit','closed','closed','','81-revision-v1','','','2018-11-07 10:14:05','2018-11-07 10:14:05','',81,'http://clinic.local/81-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(83,1,'2018-11-07 10:16:41','2018-11-07 10:16:41','How is this a real thing?\nCmon, its a loop over posts.\nIt should do the same for every post, unless the data is missing.\nBut its not missing, i just verified that it\'s there....\n\nSolution:\nthe_date(); only displays date for the first element in a set of elements posted on the same day. Something','Some posts lose their ability to display date','','inherit','closed','closed','','79-autosave-v1','','','2018-11-07 10:16:41','2018-11-07 10:16:41','',79,'http://clinic.local/79-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(84,1,'2018-11-07 10:17:27','2018-11-07 10:17:27','How is this a real thing?\r\nCmon, its a loop over posts.\r\nIt should do the same for every post, unless the data is missing.\r\nBut its not missing, i just verified that it\'s there....\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nthe_date(); only displays date for the first element in a set of elements posted on the same day. Something related to the logic in the implementation. It will fail a check if the second post shares the same date.\r\n\r\nWorkaround:\r\nUse echo get_the_date(); instead!','Some posts lose their ability to display date','','inherit','closed','closed','','79-revision-v1','','','2018-11-07 10:17:27','2018-11-07 10:17:27','',79,'http://clinic.local/79-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(86,1,'2018-11-01 09:41:47','2018-11-01 09:41:47','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, errem euismod ad qui, probo reque ne cum, et tempor dicunt commune mei. Ex delenit disputationi vim, nihil dissentias et per. No diam nostro mandamus vim. Eam cibo vive